  <p>My interests explore the intersections of seemingly disparate fields: ancient philosophy, modern technology, and the timeless nature of art. This space is less a portfolio and more an inquiry -- a place to examine the patterns that quietly connect disciplines that, on the surface, appear unrelated.</p>
  <p>I am drawn to the tension between silicon and silence, between code and contemplation. Artificial intelligence is not treated here as novelty or threat, but as a tool -- a mirror -- through which older questions reemerge in new forms. What is consciousness? What is creativity? Where does authorship begin and end? These are not new questions, only newly framed.</p>

  <h2>Ancient Wisdom, Modern Questions</h2>
  <p>From the dawn of recorded history, mystic traditions have sought to answer fundamental questions about consciousness, suffering, meaning, and reality itself. Across cultures and centuries, similar symbolic structures and insights appear again and again. This site examines those recurring patterns -- not to romanticize the past, but to test its insights against contemporary experience.</p>
  <p>Technology accelerates our lives; wisdom traditions attempt to slow them. Yet both are attempts to understand the same thing: the human condition. Here, ancient metaphors meet machine learning models. Mystic imagery sits beside command prompts. Mythological archetypes surface in algorithmic systems.</p>
  <p>The goal is not synthesis for its own sake, but clarity -- to see whether enduring truths can illuminate modern dilemmas, and whether modern tools can reveal something about ancient intuitions.</p>
  <p>This is an ongoing exploration. The questions are older than any one era, but they remain unresolved -- and perhaps that is precisely why they matter.</p>
  
  <h2>AI: A Tool for Thought</h2>
  <p>Artificial intelligence is more than just a technological marvel; it is a powerful tool for extending human creativity and analysis. Here, I examine the realistic benefits of AI as a partner in the creative process, while also acknowledging its critical limitations. True progress lies not in replacing human ingenuity, but in augmenting it, requiring careful consideration and ethical oversight.</p>

  <h2>The Digital Canvas: AI and Art</h2>
  <p>By combining a background in graphic arts and digital editing with the capabilities of AI, we can unlock new forms of expression. This website is dedicated to the practical synthesis of human artistry and machine intelligence. It is a showcase of new media created through this collaborative process, pushing the boundaries of the traditional digital canvas.</p>

